Hi Davi and Chris,

I=E2=80=99m concerned by the suggestion of meeting at 1:00 p.m. on =
Wednesday or Thursday, when we had previously agreed on 2:00 p.m. =
Wednesday.

That said, I also want to express that I believe a meeting may be =
premature. Several important points I=E2=80=99ve raised remain =
unaddressed, and without a clear written agreement on scope and =
priorities, I=E2=80=99m not sure an in-person meeting will be the best =
use of time.

To ensure we move forward in a transparent, safe, and well-coordinated =
way, I would prefer that all communication from this point be by email =
only, with responses expected within 48 hours, unless otherwise agreed.

Before any work proceeds, I would appreciate written confirmation of the =
following:

A proper assessment of the current condition of the property must come =
first. This includes external review of any safety-related issues such =
as electrical risks, structural concerns, the gas unit, possible =
asbestos (noting the area by the deck), and any mould or water damage. =
These are essential to manage health and safety risks and ensure work is =
done properly.

Initial work should focus on removing debris and internal linings to =
enable a complete assessment. Tasks like general cleaning (e.g. soft =
furnishings, heat pump cleaning, curtains, etc) that aren't related to =
preparing for assessment should not proceed yet.

For contents, I understood that the next step would be for you to =
provide a full list of inventoried items, and I would then add notes on =
anything I=E2=80=99ve already moved or flagged for inspection (e.g. =
electronics, items with lithium batteries, or those needing professional =
cleaning).

I=E2=80=99m happy to continue working together to resolve the claim =
efficiently, and these key steps need to be agreed in writing first so =
we can ensure a clear, fair, and safe process.

Kind regards,

Raffaella



